## Findings

- SQL provides a structured, reliable way to manage relational databases.
- CRUD operations, clauses, operators, and functions form the foundation of SQL usage.
- Keys enforce uniqueness and relationships.
- Functions and operators allow powerful data manipulation and analysis.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Enforce primary keys for uniqueness.
- Use foreign keys to maintain referential integrity.
- Validate and sanitize input to prevent SQL injection.
- Apply constraints (NOT NULL, data types) to enforce integrity.
- Optimize queries with indexes when using operators or functions.

